Peel and chop your @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) and @carrot{1}(peeled and chopped) into roughly 1cm pieces. Peel and chop one of your @garlic cloves{1}(peeled and chopped). Slice your @aubergine{1} into disks approximately 1cm thick.

Add @oil{1%tbsp} to a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium heat, pop your onion in the pan and cook for roughly ~{5%mins} until the onion is soft, then add your carrot and garlic and cook for a further ~{3%mins}. Add your @lamb mince{225%g} to the pan along with your @ground cinnamon{1/2%tsp}. Stir and cook until the meat is browned, then add your @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, a good grind of @pepper{good grind} and @?sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Bubble the mixture away gently for ~{15-20%mins} until the mixture is thick and tomatoey.

While the mixture is bubbling, pre-heat your #grill{} to high. Put your aubergine slices on a #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @pepper{good grind} and grill for ~{4%mins} on one side and ~{3%mins} on the other side. Take the aubergine out from under the grill and leave to the side (leave the grill on).

> The aubergine slices should be slightly browned.

You can also prepare your @ciabatta{1} while your lamb mixture is thickening up! Cut your ciabatta into slices about 1cm wide and leave to the side for later.

When the lamb mixture is nice and thick, pour it into a #baking dish{}, lay your aubergine slices on top and spoon over your @creme fraiche{1}. Spread the crème fraîche out with the back of a #spoon{} and then grate over your @parmesan cheese{2%tbsp}. Put the dish under the grill for ~{5%mins} or until the top is bubbling and brown.

While your moussaka is browning, put your @wild rocket{1%handful} in a #bowl{}, drizzle over @oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and toss.

When the 5 mins are up, remove the moussaka from under the grill and pop the ciabatta slices under, for ~{2%mins} on each side.

> Watch they don't burn!

Cut your remaining @garlic clove{1} in half, take the ciabatta out from under the grill and rub the garlic clove on the top of each ciabatta slice. You can also drizzle over a little @olive oil{a little}.

Serve your moussaka with your rocket and garlic ciabatta on the side.